@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}
<h2>@ViewBag.Title.</h2>
<h3>Welcome to BugHound, leaning and demonstration web application.</h3>
<hr />
<p>BugHound was created as an exercise for the Coder Foundry Fall 2014 Master Class. 
     It showcases the use and mastery of C#, .NET, MVC, and Bootstrap. It uses a SQL 
    backend database also designed and created specially for BugHound.   </p>

<p>To fulfill the project requirements the bug tracker software must demonstrate the following. </p>

<ol>
    <li>User Login</li>
    <li>Create User</li>
    <li>Assign / unassign users to / from Roles</li>
    <li>Create a project</li>
    <li>Assign / unassign users to / from Projects</li>
    <li>Create a Ticket</li>
    <li>Create a Ticket Comment</li>
    <li>Create a Ticket Attachement</li>
    <li>List Ticket Comments</li>
    <li>List Ticket Attachments</li>
    <li>List a Ticket's History</li>
    <li>Notify a developer / user of a newly assigned Ticket</li>
    <li>List Tickets by Owner</li>
    <li>List Tickets by Assignment</li>
    <li>List Tickets by Project</li>
    <li>All data entry / view fields must be appropriate for the type of data represented.</li>
</ol>
